== Associations with Bamboo and Architecture == Taokihonoho's role as a craftsman of sacred structures has made him a patron deity of construction, particularly in {{ill|Jōtōshiki|ja|上棟式|12=draft|12=draft}} rituals.
== Connection to the Tale of the Bamboo Cutter == The Sanuki Inbe Clan is linked to {{ill|The Tale of the Bamboo Cutter|ja|竹取物語|12=draft|12=draft}}, with suggestions that its protagonist, {{ill|Sanuki no Miyatsuko|ja|讃岐造|12=draft|12=draft}}, was inspired by the clan. Historical artifacts and local events like the "Kaguya-hime Carnival" in Takamatsu further affirm this connection.
